  <title>Cogl.PixelBuffer.new</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function new(context: <link xref="Cogl.Context">Cogl.Context</link>, size: Number(gsize), data: void): <link xref="Cogl.PixelBuffer">Cogl.PixelBuffer</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_pixel_buffer_new()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Declares a new <link xref="Cogl.PixelBuffer"/> of <code>size</code> bytes to contain arrays of
pixels. Once declared, data can be set using <link xref="Cogl.buffer_set_data"/>
or by mapping it into the application's address space using
<link xref="Cogl.buffer_map"/>.</p>  <p>If <code>data</code> isn't <code>null</code> then <code>size</code> bytes will be read from <code>data</code> and
immediately copied into the new buffer.</p>
  <p>Since 1.10</p>
